/* =========================================
   QUERY 2
   Top 10 most sold products
   ========================================= */

-- Returns top 10 products based on total quantity sold.

SELECT TOP 10
    p.product_id,
    p.product_name,
    SUM(li.quantity) AS total_quantity_sold
FROM dim_products AS p
INNER JOIN fact_order_line_items AS li
    ON p.product_id = li.product_id
GROUP BY
    p.product_id,
    p.product_name
ORDER BY total_quantity_sold DESC;

Review:
The query correctly retrieves the top 10 products based on total quantity sold and is clear and easy to understand.
The join between dim_products and fact_order_line_items is appropriate, ensuring that product details are combined
with transactional data, and the use of SUM(li.quantity) accurately aggregates total units sold per product.
The GROUP BY clause is correctly applied at the product level, and the ORDER BY total_quantity_sold DESC ensures
that the highest-selling products are returned first, which aligns with the business objective. However, the query
could be improved by considering whether products with no sales should be included (in which case a LEFT JOIN might be more appropriate).
Additionally, handling potential NULL values in quantity could improve robustness. From a business perspective, it might
also be useful to include additional context such as product category or revenue, depending on reporting needs. Overall,
the query is correct and efficient, with minor enhancements possible for completeness and flexibility.
